<title>CANADA: Merck Frosst drug gets expanded recognition.</title>
<headline>Merck Frosst drug gets expanded recognition.</headline>
<dateline>MONTREAL 1996-09-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Merck Frosst Canada Inc, a unit of Merck &amp; Co Inc, said on Thursday that Health Canada said it approved the drug Mevacor as the sole cholesterol-lowering drug to reduce cardiovascular events in patients without established heart disease.</p>
<p>Canada's Health Protection Branch recognized the effectiveness of Mevacor in treating people who have not yet experienced coronary problems, the company said.</p>
<p>-- Toronto Bureau (416) 941-8100</p>
